# floating-chat — Tab Sync & Deduplication Safety Rules

> These rules apply to every change in `floating-chat/src/`.  
> **Read `PROJECT.md`, `chat-service/DOCUMENT.md` when present, and `floating-chat/CLAUDE.md` before starting any task in this project.**
>
> Tab sync is a server-protection requirement. The goal is to prevent many browser tabs from opening many WebSocket connections and overwhelming `chat-service`.

---

## 🚨 Tab Sync is High Risk

The widget uses a **leader/follower** multi-tab model:

- **Leader tab** holds the real WebSocket; relays all WS events via `BroadcastChannel`.
- **Follower tab** has no socket; receives everything through the channel.
- Web Locks followers must probe the leader before stealing: watchdog → `LEADER_PING` → wait for `LEADER_PONG` → steal only on silence. A stale leader that receives `LEADER_TAKEOVER` must demote through `onFollow()`.

Critical files — extra care required:

| File | Risk |
|------|------|
| `src/services/tab-leader.ts` | Leader election logic (Web Locks + localStorage fallback) |
| `src/services/connection-manager.ts` | `becomeLeader()` / `becomeFollower()` — BroadcastChannel wiring |
| `src/services/tab-sync.ts` | Cross-tab UI events (`UNREAD_CLEARED`, `CHAT_OPENED`) |
| `src/service.ts` | Auth, heartbeat, queue — all communicate through tab roles |
| `src/main.ts` | Registers handlers; owns `loadHistory()` scheduling |

**Any change to these files must be tested with 2+ browser tabs open.**

---

## 🚨 Message Deduplication — Keep the Provenance-Scoped Fallback

Current live `message` and `message_sent` events carry the server id, and history carries the same id. Different real server ids are different messages even when content, direction, and timestamp match.

The content+timestamp+direction fallback is only for legacy/edge cases where one side lacks a server id, such as a live message rendered with a client fallback id before history returns the real MongoDB `_id`.

`isDuplicateMessage` MUST keep id-first deduplication and only use content fallback when either side lacks `hasServerId`:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
if (originalId) {
    if (this.sentMessageIds.has(originalId) || this.displayedMessageIds.has(originalId)) {
        return true;
    }
}
return !!this.messages.find(content + timestamp + isOwn check + missing-server-id check);

// ❌ WRONG — content fallback hides intentional repeated text with different real ids
return !!this.messages.find(content + timestamp + isOwn check);
```

**Do not apply content fallback when both messages have real server ids.**

---

## 🚨 History Loading Double-Fire

`HistoryManager.loadHistory()` always calls `resetPagination()`, which resets `isLoading = false`. Calling `loadHistory()` twice in quick succession sends two WS requests.  
**Do not add extra `loadHistory()` call sites** without accounting for this.

`addHistoricalMessages()` must register every processed `originalId` into `displayedMessageIds` so the second response is deduplicated at display time.

---

## Mandatory Test Checklist

Before marking any floating-chat change as done:

- [ ] Single tab — no regression
- [ ] Two tabs (leader + follower) — no duplicate messages
- [ ] Zombie leader takeover — silent leader is stolen, old leader demotes after wake
- [ ] Reconnect scenario — messages not duplicated after network restore
- [ ] `npm run build` passes
